    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nMigrating from https://github.com/nvim-treesitter/nvim-treesitter/issues/4754 as it doesn't require tree-sitter.\r\n\r\nWorkaround: typing `:set foldmethod=expr` on the command line triggers the folds to be created.\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n`repro.lua`:\r\n```lua\r\nvim.o.foldmethod = \"expr\"\r\nvim.o.foldexpr = \"getline(v:lnum)\"\r\n\r\nvim.keymap.set(\"i\", \"<C-x>\", function()\r\n  vim.cmd.edit(\"foldexpr.txt\")\r\nend)\r\n```\r\n\r\n`foldexpr.txt`:\r\n```txt\r\n0\r\n1\r\n2\r\n3\r\n```\r\n\r\nWill have folds:\r\n```sh\r\nnvim --clean -u repro.lua foldexpr.txt\r\n```\r\n\r\nWill not have folds (press `<C-x>` in insert mode):\r\n```sh\r\nnvim --clean -u repro.lua\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nFolds should be enabled.\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nf67517bba\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nI tried `imap <C-x> <C-o>:e repro.lua<CR>` but that doesn't reproduce in Neovim nor Vim.\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nmacos 13.4.1\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nkitty 0.28.1\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-kitty\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nbuild from repo",
