            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Interesting; seems tricky since the opened file is opened in normal mode. But perhaps the `FileType` happens before entering normal mode?\r\n\r\nProbably it would be nice to update folds on `InsertLeave` - IDK if that needs to be a core behavior, but something the user can program. For example, right now if you manually type 0 1 2 3 4 in that file you can't fold it later. If you select and do `dp` then it gets folded. That might be confusing.\r\n\r\n> Maybe there needs to be a way to force-update folds now?\r\n\r\nI guess this is what `:set foldmethod=expr` accomplishes, but it looks janky",
